inn1.comm: Irfan Pathan takes the new ball, starts with a delivery wide outside off
back of a length, on middle and leg this time, Bopara tries to work it square but misses it
Irfan get the ball to swing back into the batsman, thuds into Bopara's pads and runs away for four between the keeper and leg slip
short of a length, on off stump this time, watchfully defended by Bopara
similar delivery from Irfan, Bopara taps it back to the bowler
four more leg byes for England, more swing for Irfan, and that takes the ball towards leg, hits the pad and races away fine
length ball outside off, Cook shoulders arms to it
another delivery outside off, Cook doesn't offer a shot to that one either
Zaheer getting the ball to shape away from the left-hand batsman here, again Zaheer bowls wide of off and Cook lets it go
slants into Cook's pads this time, stifled appeal for lbw but that sliding down leg
a touch shorter and Cook uses the width provided to deflect it to the third man boundary, quick outfield here in Cuttack
and this was too wide outside off for the umpire's liking
length ball on off, Cook gets on the front and works it towards point
on a length just outside off, moved in a bit to Cook, big shout for lbw but umpire signals it was high
length ball moving away from the left-hander, pushed towards point, Suresh Raina and Yuvraj Singh converge on the ball, neither manage to field it
good line and length from Irfan, defended towards point
full and wide, punched towards point
pitches on off and comes in a touch to Bopara, who defends it cautiously back to the bowler
shorter ball, pitches on middle and comes in a hint, Bopara looks to play it square, misses the ball, massive appeal from Pathan, turned down but Hawkeye says it would have hit
defended into the off side
length ball just outside off, Bopara punches it down the ground for his first four, England maintaining a good run-rate here
hit hard towards cover but doesn't beat the field
back of a length, angling across Bopara, gets the inside edge and, fortunately for Bopara, doesn't crash into his stumps
plays a full delivery on off to mid on
short ball outside off, pushed towards Suresh Raina at cover, would have been tight if there had been a direct hit, England pick up an overthrow as well
defended back to the bowler
length ball from Irfan, tapped back to the bowler by Bopara
similar delivery from Irfan, Bopara gets on the front foot and defends
on middle and leg this time, Bopara works it wristily but doesn't beat the man at midwicket
strays on the pads again, glanced to fine leg where Ishant Sharma does well to cut if off
outside off, short of a length, Bopara smacks it hard towards cover, straight to the fielder
length ball, coming back into Bopara, who pushes it towards mid-off
back of a length delivery, pitching on middle and going across Bopara, who gets the leading edge towards mid-on as he tries to work it to point
glanced to fine leg for a single
pitched up, angling into Cook's pads, Cook flicks it away towards square leg
shorter ball, on middle and leg, thuds into Bopara's gloves and trickles away towards short fine leg
very wide outside off to Cook, and moving further away

Cook's gone! a length delivery but wide outside off from Zaheer, Cook chases after it, gets the outside edge, straight to first slip, not a delivery Zaheer would have expected to get a wicket with and he has a bit of a sheepish grin on his face
length ball, angling across Pietersen, who shoulders arms to it
super shot from Bopara, a short of a length delivery moving back into him, great timing from Bopara as he pushes it through covers
similar ball, pushed towards cover, straight to the fielder this time
strays onto the pads and an easy single as Bopara glances it to fine leg
Irfan brings out the bouncer, Pietersen goes for the pull, gets a top edge, gets him a boundary as it flies high over the keeper
length ball outside off, mistimed back to the bowler
another streaky boundary for Pietersen, outside off and he goes for the drive, gets a thick outside edge which flies wide off the slips and races away for four
pitched up, width provided, and Bopara guides it towards third man
nice, tight line from Zaheer, Pietersen moves across his stumps  and decides to shoulder arms
on middle and leg this time, fantastic timing from Kevin Pietersen as he turns it towards midwicket, lightning outfield at this ground
the timing isn't as good on that one as he gets on the front foot and pats it down the ground
pitched up, Pietersen walks cross his stumps and flicks it for four to square leg, slightly dangerous shot that, he's a goner if he misses when he shuffling across
gets across the stumps again as he defends a slower delivery from Zaheer
Irfan still getting some movement into the right-hander, length ball and Bopara pushes it towards mid-on
slower full delivery from Irfan, rolling his fingers across the seam, Bopara blocks it
full and swinging in, driven to mid off
back of a length, on middle and leg, Pietersen collects another leg-side boundary, glancing it to the left of Ishant at fine leg
on middle and leg again, Pietersen has no trouble guiding that to fine leg
better line this time, just outside off, Bopara cuts it towards cover point and the batsmen pinch a quick single
length ball on off, Bopara gets on the front foot and drives it to extra cover, straight to the fielder
slower ball from Zaheer, pitched up, and Bopara cracks that through extra cover for a boundary
full ball again, but wide outside off, thwacked by Bopara straight to Sehwag at short cover, would be harsh to call that a chance as it was travelling real fast
Bopara backs away and steers it behind point
Gone this time, the end of Bopara, tried to drive it on the up, goes straight to Yuvraj Singh at backward point, second wicket for Zaheer
defended off the back foot towards cover point
straight with a length ball outside off which Pietersen lets go off watchfully
short of a length ball, Pietersen drives off the front foot, superb placement and timing has it racing away through the covers
outside off and Pietersen shoulders arms to that one
back of a length and outside off, Kevin Pietersen offers no shot to that one either
140.7 kmh from Ishant, length ball in the channel just outside off, Pietersen isn't interested in that one
similar line, Pietersen walks across the stumps to work it to midwicket, wanted a single but wisely decides against it
full and outside off, driven to mid-off
back of a length, on off, Collingwood pats it back to the bowler off the back foot
fuller ball, some width to free the arms as well, Collingwood goes after it but doesn't beat the fielder at cover
angling across Collingwood, and he defends to point
more defence from Collingwood, blocks a off stump delivery
driven to mid-off by Collingwood this time, straight to the fielder
length delivery, Pietersen tries to drive it but mistimes it back to the bowler
well outside off, and left alone by the batsman
back of a length, Ishant maintains a superb line, just outside off, Pietersen is content to shoulder arms to that one
similar line from Ishant, Pietersen moves across the stumps to flick it to fine leg, a touch risky for a single
well wide outside off, Collingwood lets that go through to the keeper
short ball, not enough room to cut but Collingwood attempts to anyway, mistimes the stroke and it dribbles away towards point
back of a length, on middle and off, Pietersen works it towards mid-on
pitched up, Irfan gets it to swing in to Collingwood who taps it to mid-on
a touch outside off, Collingwood shuffles across the stumps to play it, only manages to defend it towards cover
on middle and leg, and Collingwood gets off the mark by glancing that one
played with soft hands by Pietersen towards cover, batsmen steal a quick single
another single as Irfan strays onto leg stump, Colliongwood turns it away behind square
Collingwood shuffles again to work it through the leg side, only manages an inside edge onto his pads
well outside off, Collingwood tries to cut that one but doesn't make contact
length delivery on middle and off, Collingwood defends it cautiously
length ball outside off, and that kept very low, skids underneath Collingwood's bat, and bounces before reaching the keeper, that was bowled at 138kph
shorter ball, more width, Collingwood tries to cut again, but the ball goes under his flashing blade
poor ball to end the over, half-volley on middle and leg, and Collingwood helps himself to an easy boundary, turning it towards square leg
Tosses up his first delivery, pitched outside off and turned in, Pietersen gets a big stride in as he tries to defend, hits his pad though
tossed up on middle, clipped to mid wicket
back of a length, outside off, Pietersen pushes it towards cover poitn, thinks of a single but decides against it
straying onto leg, but Pietersen doesn't capitalise as he only manages to push it towards midwicket
down leg again, and Pietersen sweeps him for a single
Flighted delivery to end the over, outside off, and Collingwood defends it to point
short of a length on off, Pietersen gets a long way across to play it to midwicket for a single
length ball, on middle and leg, Collingwood drives it to mid-on for a single
on offstump, Pietersen works it away to square leg
shorter ball outside off, punched to cover
outside leg stump from Yuvraj, nudged to fine leg
maintains that line, and this one is clipped towards square leg for another single
length ball outside off, batsman walks across and drives it to mid-on
topspinner from Harbhajan, defended towards cover
lot of turn for Harbhajan, Pietersen misses the ball after coming down the track, gets some pad on it though which saves him
full and very wide outside off, Pietersen attempts to sweep, gets the bottom edge and the ball trickles away towards third man
on off, defended watchfully by Pietersen
turns it to short mid wicket
flat down the pads and another easy, shuffled single to leg
slows the pace, tosses it on off stump, defended to point
flat on the stumps and whipped away to midwicket for one
tossed up on the stumps and KP defends
flat on the stumps, turned away for one
shuffles and works another easy single
very flat and wide down the pads, Dhoni collects
flat on the stumps, worked for a single
outside off, well wide, tries to sweep and mistimes it
tossed up and defended baclk
gets across and works this ball to square leg for one
big turn down the pads, he mistimes the attempted nudge

poor fielding by Sehwag! Collingwood skips down and clips the ball over mid-on, it lands in the deep and rolls towards the ropes, two fielders converge, Sehwag gets there first and stops it, then stumbles and lets the ball dribble into the ropes
walks down and drills this very hard and flat down past the stumps, Sharma dives at deep mid-on and does well to take some pace off that shot
tossed up and Collingwood defends it back to Yuvraj
slower through the air, a tad full, and driven into the covers
turns this one to short fine leg, Collingwood sends him back
quicker arm ball, KP mistimes the shot to backward point
comes out and takes it on the full, driving to midwicket for one
walks across his stumps and turns it to square leg
flatter ball on middle and off, Collingwood defends
sweeps it from off stump down to Kohli at deep square
tossed up wide, KP waits for it and steers past point for one
comes out and chips it over midwicket, falls safe, Sehwag fields
shorter, flatter, and defended to backward point
tossed up from Yuvraj, length ball on off, Collingwood blocks it back to the bowler
nudged to square leg
defended off the front foot to the off side
tries to drive it firmly down the ground, mistimes it back to the bowler
gets a single this time, driven to long-off
arm ball to end the over, Pietersen attempts the late cut but misses
back of a length outside off, punched down to long-off
fuller this time, but a similar stroke from the batsman gets another single to long-off
defended off the front foot to the off side
fullish and outside off, Collingwood goes for the sweep but is rapped on his back pad, there's appeal but it struck him outside off
on middle and leg, fullish delivery, pushed down to long-on
flighted and held the length back a bit, defended watchfully off the front foot to the bowler
pitched up, outside off, Collingwood's slog sweep just about clears the man at deep midwicket and lands just within the boundary, several replays needed to determine whether that was a four or a six
quicker ball, on middle and leg, Collingwood punches it down the ground
big stride in as Pietersen defends, gets the inside edge and dribbless towards midwwicket
turned to the leg side
driven to wide long-on for an easy single
on a length, outside off, Collingwood taps it towards cover point
strays onto leg again, another easy single to mid-on
uses his feet as works it to midwicket, nice placement there give him enough time to take two
length ball on off, swept powerfully by Pietersen towards fine leg
just outside off, Collingwood defends that off the front foot
stepped down, nearly beaten by the topspinner, but managed to get some bat on it
blocked back to the bowler
width provided and Pietersen guides it to third man to bring up his fifty
tossed up, Collingwood comes down the track to get to the pitch of the ball and smashes that through extra cover for four
guided towards gully for a single
on middle and leg, Pietersen pounds it down the ground, Yuvraj dives and sticks his hands out but the ball doesn't stick, very, very tough chance that
watchfully blocked off the front foot
tries to sweep again, doesn't quite get hold of it, ball rolls away to  short fine leg
a full, quick ball just outside off, Pietersen jumps across the stumps to sweep but it hits hom on the boot and runs away down past the keeper for four
much shorter ball, Pietersen tries to sweep from outside off again, gets a bootom edge towards midwicket
Collingwood also shuffles across to nudge the ball towards square leg
played with soft hands towards cover point, thought of going for a single but decided against it
a bit of bounce for Yuvraj, Pietersen backs away and slap it towards cover
length ball outside off, Collingwood dances down and chips it over mid-off for a single
well outside off, Pietersen had already backed away from leg stump and can't get any power into his shot
outside off again, Pietersen stands his ground and punches it towards cover
driven to long off
quicker, flatter ball, turned to midwicket
on off stump, Pietersen comes down the track and cracks it to the right of long-on for a boundary
and that's a superb shot to bring up 3000 runs for Pietersen, comes down the track and slogs it over long-on for a six
sweeps from outside off to deep square leg
outside off, tries to work it behind point, goes straight to the fielder
Collingwood goes for the drive, but only gets a thin inside edge onto his pads

Collingwood's gone! Superb catch from Zaheer, Collingwood stepped out to loft him over long-on, didn't get hold of it, and it flew towards Zaheer and was dying on him but he managed to take a low catch
short of a length, outside off, Pietersen walks down the track and drives it towards long-on
full ball, well outside off, Flintoff is content to let that go
gets on the front foot and drives it to cover, straight to the fielder so there's no run available
Flintoff's gone! big wicket for India, pitched up, a bit of width, Flintoff goes for the drive, only gets an outside edge which flies straight to Sachin Tendulkar at slip
length ball, a touch outside off, Shah lets that go by playing inside the line of that one
quick delivery to end the over, 142.7 kmh, just outside off and had Shah feeling for it
short ball, Pietersen gives himself room to punch that through the covers
pitched up, Shah gets a big stride in as he plays it towards cover
Pietersen feigns as if he's going to back away, stand his ground, Yuvraj fires it on middle, defended by Pietersen
patted into the covers
faster ball,  worked towards the leg side
back away to drive a full ball on leg stump to long-on
full on middle, flicked towards midwicket
q bit of width provided, Pietersen pushes it with soft hands to covers for a single
outside off again, Shah cuts it hard but straight to the fielder at cover point
oooh! similar delivery to the one that got Flintoff, Shah's attempted drive results in a thick outside edge which flies wide of Tendulkar at slip
much tighter line this time, closer to off, defended by Shah towards cover
pitched up, on middle and leg, wonderfully timed drive from Shah, Yusuf Pathan puts in a dive from mid-off to cut that off
short ball, carries on with the angle beyond leg, Pietersen backs away but can't get it away
slower in the air, just outside off and Pietersen was groping for that one, gets beaten
backs away and punches to cover, straight to the fielder
well outside off, Pietersen goes for the sweep, gets a bottom edge on to it
much quicker from Yuvraj, 102kmh, Pietersen tries to sweep from outside off, rapped on the pads but outside the line
this time he connects and the sweep to midwicket fetches him a single
lucky for Pietersen, an attempted off drive gets the inside edge and races away for four to fine leg
moves around in the crease before clipping it to midwicket
good length, just outside off, played to mid-on for a single
slower ball, pitched up outside off, driven to long-on

wide outside off, Shah's attempted cut gets a thick top edge, it flies towards Zaheer at third man and is dropping, Zaheer isn't sure whether to charge in for the or hang back and save the runs, doesn't get there in time for the catch, and can't stop it from trickling over the boundary either
driven firmly towards cover, straight to the fielder
slow and outside off, went through the sweep shot early and missed it
a tad quicker dabbed to square leg
just outside off, played with soft hands towards cover for a single
nudged towards square leg, Dhoni is quickly onto the ball to prevent the single
tapped back to the bowler
tossed up, on off, defended off the front foot
back of a length, a touch outside off, defended cautiously by Shah off the backfoot
nothing cautious about that shot, short ball, well outside off, Shah goes for the cut with little footwork but the ball goes under the bat
drifts on to the pads, easily glanced for a single by Shah
full ball, on middle and off, firmly driven down to long-on
beaten, Shah tried to dab that down to third man, but that ball just moved a touch away from him and he is unable connect with it
good, tight line from Ishant, on a length and on off, tapped to mid-off
massive appeal for lbw, Pietersen walks across the stumps and tries to sweep, gets hit on the pads but that was well outside the line of off
patted to the leg side by Pietersen
driven down to long-on for a single
tossed up, length ball, Shah pushes it towards mid-on
shorter, on middle, and some turn for Harbhajan, Shah plays it to midwicket
on leg stump, Pietersen sweep to midwicket for a single
back of a length slower ball on off, Pietersen defends it back to the bowler
on leg stump, tries to flick it but doesn't connect and the ball dribbles to the leg side off his pad
pitched on a length on leg, Shah backs away and tries to power it down the ground, but it was a slower ball and he mistimes it towards mid-on
a bit of width and pushed it towards cover for a single
well outside off, Shah tries to slog it over midwicket, not the best shot to a ball more than a foot outside off, doesn't make contact
that was a much better shot, cracked through mid-off for a boundary, the fielders had no chance of stopping that
full, flat and fast on legstump, turned to the legside
slower, flighted delivery, defended off the front foot
outside off, driven down the ground, Harbhajan dives and tips the ball towards the fielder at mid-on
opens the face of the bat to place it behind point
backs away and drives down the ground, this time Harbhajan's dive doesn't stop the ball but there is a fielder at long-on
well outside leg stump, flicked towards midwicket for a single to end Harbhajan's spell
a touch short, angling across the batsman, who is beaten by that one
full ball, defended back to the bowler

full and outside off, Shah tries to crash that through the off side, Raina was the fielder at extra cover and a direct hit from him could have make things tight for Pietersen who was sent back by Shah
Smash! length ball, a golf swing dispatches the ball straight down the ground
in the blockhole, on middle and off, Shah just about manage to dig that one out towards mid-off
back of a length, on leg stump, nudged to square leg, straight to the fielder and that means only five runs have come of the first over of this Powerplay
full and outside off, thrashed down the ground, but just the single as it is cut off by the long-on fielder
low full toss on off, punched towards mid-on
slower ball, 115kmh, short and outside off, Shah doesn't get the timing right as he tries to slam that to midwicket
full ball outside off, Suresh Raina misfields at extra cover but there's no extra run
fullish and well outside off, Shah targets the spot wide of mid-on but again doesn't quite get hold of the ball
Ishant keeps it full and outside off, Pietersen pushes it to mid-on for a single
full toss on offstump, Pietersen shuffles across his stumps and punches it to mid-off
shortish ball angling across Shah, he walks across his stumps and turns it to midwicket for a single
yorker on off stump, all Pietersen can do is dig it out back to the bowler
low full toss on middle this time, Pietersen flicks it to midwicket, great timing on that, fetches him two
punched down the ground by Pietersen to collect another two runs
whipped to the left of mid-on for a single
Ishant keeps it full, slower ball, and Pietersen pats it to the off side for a single
another slower ball, this time it's dispatched for four through the covers,
Shah decides he still wants to swat it over midwicket from more than a foot outside off, doesn't make contact
outside off again, Shah shuffles across and nudges it towards midwicket
length ball, a lot of width provided again, Pietersen drives it crisply to long-off where Irfan does the fielding
full ball outside off, Shah again jumps across his stumps to nurdle it towards midwicket
shortish ball on leg stump, Shah tries to help it to fine leg but doesn't make contact
full and outside off, Pietersen squeezes it out towards cover point
Zaheer keeps the length full, on middle and off this time, pushed towards mid-off
Pietersen plays it gently towards mid-on, batsmen go for a quick single, there's a direct hit from Ishant at the non-striker's end but Pietersen had made his ground
full again, driven down to long-off for a single
a touch shorter, on middle and leg, whipped away towards midwicket
Pietersen walks down the track to a slower ball, and his attempted heave gets and edge but it doesn't carry through to the keeper
shows the full face of the bat as he drives it straight down the ground
low, full toss just outside off, slashed through cover for a single
flicked towards midwicket from just outside off, another single
another single, this time to long-on, where Harbhajan does the fielding
Another slower ball from Irfan , angling across Pietersen, who couldn't connect after walking down the track
short of a length and outside off, slogged by Shah to mid-on, no run
that's better from Shah, backs away a bit to make some room and hammers a length delivery to the mid-on boundary, one-bounce four
pitched up and outside off, Shah cracks that one through the covers for another boundary
driven firmly to long-off, placement wasn't good enough to get a boundary
and that's Pietersen's century, a full ball on middle and leg and Pietersen punches it down to long-on, that's his seventh ODI century
Another milestone as Shah brings up his fifty by guiding the ball towards third man for two
Pietersen back away and slaps an outside off delivery to cover for a single
Shot! length ball on middle and off, and Shah clubs it down the ground, dead straight for a four

slower ball from Irfan, Shah picks it up late but manages ot get it away to square leg, Yusuf Pathan does the fielding, and the third umpire is called for to decide whether Shah has made it back for the second, and he has
a touch outside off and that's driven to deep cover
short ball, on middle and leg, Pietersen charges down the ground and tries to pull it, doesn't time it well and it rolls towards mid-on
slow, full ball outside off, Shah doesn't pick that one up and doesn't offer a shot as it goes through to the keeper
low, full toss on offstump, Pietersen gives himself room as he clubs it to sweeper cover
length ball, just outside off, Shah tries to smack that5 out of the ground, gets it high on the bat, and it balloons in the air before landing safely near mid-on
pulled powerfully by Pietersen, and the fielder at square leg has some fielding to do
back of a length delivery, played with soft hands towards  gully
slower full toss, Pietersen slogs it towards square leg, Rohit Sharma does not pick up the ball as it lands a few yards away from him, manages to field it though
full toss and that gets the treatment from Shah, swung away wide of the fielder at midwicket
driven powerfully down to long-on for a single
length ball outside off, Pietersen flatbats it to long-on for a single
a bit of width and that is pushed towards cover point for a single
length ball on off, Shah clubs it down the ground, long-on does the fielding
pitched up, just outside off, Pietersen cracks that down the down for a straight four
short ball from Irfan, completely deceives Pietersen, whose attempt to hack the ball away gets the top edge and lands just wide of the bowler.

inn2.comm: back of a length, outside off, just a hint of swing away from Sehwag, who leaves the ball alone
similar length, homing into on off stump this time, Sehwag shows us his front-foot defence
shifts his line to middle, Sehwag pushes it towards mid-off
shortish ball, well outside off, you shouldn't be bowling there to Sehwag, he crashes that square for four
much better line, around off stump, Sehwag defends it off his front foot
drops it a touch shorter, Sehwag moves onto the backfoot and pats it back to the bowler
good start from Broad, tight line outside off, good length Tendulkar defends to cover
a touch shorter and on middle and leg, Tendulkar helps it to fine leg for a single
good length, on middle stump, blocked back to the bowler by Sehwag
and another hit-me ball for Sehwag, back of a length and width provided, Sehwag slaps that through cover for four
Broad retort is a bouncer, Sehwag ducks under it, and the umpire deems that that was too high
short of a length on off and middle, Sehwag gets on the backfoot  and pats it back to the bowler
similar length but on leg stump, Sehwag doesn't capitalise on that, flicking it straight to the fielder at midwicket
Harmison is getting just a bit of movement, but that was too wide outside off to interest or trouble Tendulkar
closer to off this time, on a length, Tendulkartries to cut that one but gets a bottom edge and the ball trickles away to the offside
Tendulkar gets a nice, confident stride in as he defends a length delivery outside off
gets behind that one and defends confidently to the off side
good over so far from Harmison, keeping it on a good line and length, Tendulkar defends it to cover
another good ball to complete the maiden, Tendulkar gets forward and pats it back to the bowler
Broad starts with a poor delivery, well down leg, Sehwag manages to get some glove on it and it runs away for four to fine leg
on middle this time, Sehwag whips it away towards midwicket for a single
in the channel outside off, Tendulkar gets forward and defends to the off side
a streaky boundary for Tendulkar, a shortish ball outside off from Broad keeps a touch low, Tendulkar shapes for the cut but gets a bottom edge which races away to the fine-leg boundary
beaten this time, pitching on a length and moving away from Tendulkar, who fails to make contact with his attempted defensive prod
much better from Tendulkar, gets behind the line of the ball and defends it
pitched up by Harmison, Sehwag tries to work that behind point but it goes straight to the fielder
Harmison provides Sehwag width, and the batsman doesn't need a second invitation to slash that over the infield and behind point for four
much better line from Harmison, on off stump, Sehwag defends that off the backfoot
an uncharacteristic shot from Sehwag, that was again wide outside off from Harmison, Sehwag tries to pull it but the ball keeps a bit low and Sehwag doesn't connect
Harmison tests Sehwag with a bouncer, Sehwag gets out of the way, again that's deemed a wide
pitched up, on middle and off, Sehwag picks that up and slams it wide of mid-on for a four, didn't quite middle it but has enough to go to the boundary
poor ball to finish the over, straying down the leg side and Sehwag gets an easy boundary, helping it on its way to fine leg
back of a length, tight line outside off, Tendulkar defends off the back foot
similar length, slightly wider than the previous ball, but it was still too close to cut, Tendulkar cuts anyway, manages to get it down to third man for a single
on off stump, Sehwag plays it to backward point where Paul Collingwood misfields to allow a single
a touch of movement in towards Tendulkar, and that ball kept a bit low as well, Tendulkar's drive gets an inside edge and runs towards fine leg
slaps a wide delivery hard, but straight to the fielder, Sehwag is unhappy to have missed out on that
slightly short, on off and middle, Sehwag dismisses that to the midwicket boundary with a pull
Harmison gets it on Tendulkar's pads, a leg bye results as the ball trickles away towards square leg
shortish ball, on middle and leg, kept a bit lower than Sehwag expected, his attempted pull ends as a bottom-edge onto his pads
short ball on leg stump, Tendulkar works that away wristily behind square on the leg side
pitched up by Harmison, driven firmly back to the bowler, who shies at the stumps, eliciting a roar from the crowd
bangs in the bouncer, wide outside off, Tendulkar goes for the cut, gets a top edge which lands safely near sweeper cover
length ball, Sehwag tries to defend but the ball sneaks past his bat, that stayed a touch low as well
starts off with a short of length ball, outside off, Tendulkar mistimes it to mid-off
slightly wider from Harmison, Tendulkar goes for the cut, gets a bottom edge and Prior makes a good stop
Shot! just a push from Tendulkar, and that races away through covers
length ball, angling into offstump, Sehwag defends it watchfully to the off side
not that wide from Flintoff, Sehwag throws his bat at it anyway, it flies towards third man, and reaches the fielder on teh first bounce
beaten, cracking delivery to end the over, in the channel outside off, Tendulkar goes for the drive, but plays inside the line of the ball
start with length delivery, wide outside off, thats defended towards cover
a touch shorter on off, Sehwag walks across the stumps and attempts a wristy flick, timing wasn't great on that
whistling down the legside, Sehwag was looking to send that into orbit, doesn't make contact though
slower ball, checked his shot, plays it straight to mid-off
digs in the bouncer, outside off, Sehwag goes for the pull, again doesn't quite get hold of it and it goes towards midwicket
England appeal for a caught-behind, a short ball on Sehwag's pads goes through to the keeper, no bat involved in that one
fullish ball on leg stump, Sehwag nudges it away towards square leg for a couple
good start to the over, back of a length ball that cramps Tendulkar for room, he defends it towards cover point

Tendulkar's leading a charmed life here, similar ball as the previous one, Tendulkar goes for the drive, gets a thick outside edge which doesn't carry to Shah at slip, Tendulkar gets another streaky boundary
magnificent shot from Tendulkar, pitched up from Flintoff, on middle and Tendulkar pushes it down the ground for a boundary, there was no follow-through on that shot
outside off and Tendulkar lets that one go through to the keeper
drifts onto Tendulkar's pads, full ball and Tendulkar helps himself to a single by working that behind square
Full delivery from Samit Patel, pushed towards cover
Sehwag dances down the track and tries to slam that out of the ground, doesn't get hold of it and it runs away towards midwicket
driven to short cover, straight to the fielder
length ball, just outside off, Tendulkar opens tha face of the bat to steer it very fine to third man for a boundary
this time Tendulkar gets an inside edge which  runs away towards square leg, good running fetches them two
fullish ball on middle and leg, Tendulkar flicks that towards deep midwicket for a single
on the pads and it is turned away to fine leg
back of a length, tight line just outside off, Sehwag opens the face of teh bat as he plays it towards point
Flintoff's not giving Sehwag any room to work with, this one was again on off and Sehwag can only push it back to the bowler
ooh!, slightly wider this time, gets Sehwag onto the front foot and his tries to defend but is beaten
length ball, driven to deep cover by Sehwag for a single
slightly short, well outside off, Tendulkar tries to crash that behind point but Collingwood is there to field it
turning in towards Sehwag, who back away and punches it to cover
whistles down the leg side, he'll have to bowl that one again
again Sehwag backs away to given himself room and drives it through covers for a boundary
SHOT! in the slot for Sehwag, gets down on one knee and slams that over midwicket for a huge six
this was fuller from Swann, Sehwag gets his front foot out of the way and smashes it through cover
comes down the track to try bring up his fifty with a six, doesn't get hold of it but it still flies over mid-off for a four
and again, Sehwag gets this over extra cover, where Alaistar Cook runs across to prevent another boundary
strays onto the pads, Tendulkar joins in the act with a wonderfully timed flick behind square on the leg side
much better delivery, back of a length, on off, forces Tendulkar onto the backfoot and he pushes it towards midwicket
that one kept low, shortish ball, some width provided, Sehwag goes for his favourite cut shot but the ball goes under his bat
on a length, on middle and leg, Sehwag blocks it back to the bowler
and again, this time on middle and off, Sehwag is opened up as he plays it towards point
that will worry the Indian batsmen, that ball barely got up off the floor, luckily for Sehwag that back-of-a-length ball was directed outside off, Matt Prior has a tough time collecting that
overpitched, on middle and leg, Tendulkar has no trouble turning that away to midwicket to bring up India's 100
fires in the bouncer, and that was too high for the umpire's liking
just outside off, Sehwag steers that towards third man for a single
full toss on off stump, Tendulkar flicks that towards deep square leg
overpitched on middle and leg, Sehwag whips that towards midwicket
flicked for another single towards midwicket
full ball outside off, Sehwag defends it towards mid-off
Flintoff starts off bang on target, back of a length, on off stump, Tendulkar defends off the back foot
A bit of width provided, Tendulkar tries to run that down to third man but deosn't make contact with the ball
Flintoff reverts to his offstump line, Tendulkar blocks it back to the bowler off the front foot
well outside off, Tendulkar places that to perfection, behind Collingwood at backward point and wide of Broad at third man
another ball that stays low, again England are unlucky that the ball wasn't directed on the stumps, it was just outside off
beaten by a beauty from Flintoff, length ball on middle and off, Tendulkar tries to flick it to the leg side but is beaten, the ball sails over the stumps to the keeper
Sehwag pushes that to cover for a single
a touch outside off, Tendulkar plays that towards point
Sehwag is given room to work with again, and he cuts that behind point for four, that rockets away to the boundary
beautiful straight drive, it was a length ball on of and middle, Sehwag punches it back past the bowler for another four
overpitched outside off, Sehwag places that through the cover to get himself a couple
played with soft hands by Sehwag towards cover, batsmen go through for a wuick single, a direct hit would have had caught Tendulkar well short
pushed to covers for a single
short of a length from Flintoff, Tendulkar takes his bottom hand off the bat as he defends
Tendulkar closes the face of the bat as he tries to work it to leg, gets an inside edge onto the pads
down the leg side, there's a big appeal for caught-behind but Sehwag's bat wasn't involved in that
steers it to third man for a single
Tendulkar tips it towards point and thinks of a single but, perhaps after last over's suicidal single, decides against it
way down the leg side
On the pads, Sehwag drops it to the leg side and runs through for a single
Samit persists with the leg-stump line, Tendulkar drives it down the ground and ambles through for a single
These two batsmen are happy taking the singles, there's another one, driven to long-on
slower delivery, tossed up, Tendulkar makes room and drives that towards sweeper cover
Full ball on leg stump, Sehwag reverse sweeps that for a boundary
charges down the track, looking to smash it out of the park, Samit drags it short and Sehwag can only play it back to the bowler
Tendulkar gets his 90th half-century in ODIs by poking that delivery towards backward point
driven through covers for a single
short a length ball, Tendulkar comes down the track and pushes it towards cover point
high full toss outside off, Tendulkar goes for the cut, gets the bottom edge

Tendulkar's gone! Harmison gets the breakthrough, and a much-needed one too, that was a length ball, Tendulkar tried to smash that to midwicket, but misses the ball which crashes into middle and off stump, the crowd are stunned into silence
gets off the mark with a glance towards backward square leg
full ball on legstump, Sehwag works it away to wide long-on for a single
Yuvraj gets on the front foot and blocks it back to the bowler
worked away towards point for a single
another single, this time to midwicket
and one more as Yuvraj punches it to cover
another single to complete the over, Sehwag pushes it to midwicket
a bit wide outside off, Sehwag jabs it through cover for yet another single
length ball on off, Yuvraj defends it confidently off the back foot
back of a length, good, tight line outside off, Yuvraj taps it back to the bowler
on middle and leg, full ball, easy pickings for Yuvraj, who turns it to midwicket for a single
bangs in the bouncer, which doesn't get up as high as Sehwag thought it would, he manages to duck under anyway
half-volley on legstump, Sehwag collects another boundary, the placement and timing on that leg glance were perfect
fullish, outside off, driven by Yuvraj to long-off
ooh, that was close, Sehwag gets an inside-edge as he goes for the big drive, it runs away to the fine leg boundary. and he moves into the nineties
length ball on ball, Sehwag defends it into the covers
tries to slog that over midwicket, gets the toe end of the bat and it dribbles away to the off side
way down the leg side, Prior does a good job collecting that one
very close to offstump, Sehwag decides to steer it to third man anyway, picks up a single for his effort
Yuvraj's gone, Bopara strikes, a soft dismissal for Yuvraj, the ball might have stopped on him a bit, and his attempted on-drive lobs into Bopara's hands

Sehwag's gone, that's another massive wicket for England, Stuart Broad gets Sehwag lbw, that ball came into Sehwag, who tried to play it to down the ground off the back foot, he missed and the umpire thought that was out,  that would have definitely been missed leg
well outside off, Raina lets that go
much closer to the stumps, Raina defends cautiously
a bit of width provided and Raina gets off the mark with a poke towards point
beaten as he tries to drive, that was another ball that kept low
Dhoni gets his first runs by working the ball towards midwicket
back of a length, just outside off, Dhoni gets behind the line of the ball and defends it towards mid-off
Dhoni swishes at a wide delivery from Flintoff, doesn't make contact
Dhoni comes across his stumps and opens the face as tries to work it to third man, this one goes straight to backward point
short of length again, in the channel outside off, Dhoni shoulders arms to that one
pitched up on middle and off, Dhoni again shuffles across the stumps and defends back to the bowler
worked through the gap in the covers for a single, that's the only run of the over
length ball, Dhoni waltzes down the track and jabs it towards cover
short and wide, Dhoni doesn't make the most of it, his cut is fielded by Collingwood at point
a bit wide outside off, Raina prods it to covers, and there's a lot of confused calling before the batsmen decide to go for the single
Dhoni can't find the gap as he tries to dispatch an outside off delivery behind point
well outside off, Dhoni is content to watch that one through to the keeper
full length, on middle, Dhoni taps it back to the bowler
slightly wide outside off, Raina goes for the cut but misses it
on middle and off, length ball, Raina defends it watchfully back to the bowler
fullish delivery, outside off, Raina mistimes it to mid-on
pushes it towards point, but straight to the fielder
full and wide, Raina stays on the backfoot as he works that to cover
a maiden over, Raina tries to power that to long-on but doesn't get the timing it, and the ball dribbles to the left of the bowler
driven to mid-off, no run

outside off and Raina tries to drive it through cover, no footwork as he plays and he gets beaten
A bit wide and Raina gets his first boundary by guiding it behind backward point
short ball, outside off, Raina isn't quite sure what to do with, ends up offering an ungainly defence off the back foot
shortish again, fended it down to the off side
full ball on the leg stump, Dhoni flicks it to square leg, superb running helps them get two
length ball, some width provided, Dhoni drives it through cover, Anderson does a great job cutting off the boundary
defended back to the bowler
overpitched, on middle and leg, Dhoni plays it with soft hands towards mid-on and a single is pinched
full ball again, on middle, Raina drives it down the ground, "Make it two" was the call from Dhoni, and then get two
blocked back to the bowler by Raina
Flintoff pegs away at that back of a length, Dhoni gets forward and defends
shortish ball on off, Dhoni walks across the stumps and closes the face of the bat and gets two runs to midwicket
Come down the track the time, and superb timing sends that length ball to the long-on boundary
good, tight line, Dhoni defends it towards cover
just a touch of movement away from Dhoni, who goes for the big drive, only to be beaten
length ball outside off, that keep low, Dhoni shoulders arms to that one
driven off the back foot to deep cover
overpitched, just outside off, Dhoni drives it firmly down to long-off
short of a length, angling across Raina, who defends cautiously
lovely shot, length ball from Bopara, the extra cover drive was away from his body but the timing was wonderful and it races to the boundary
slower ball, out of the back of the hand, Raina spots it late but manages to play it back to the bowler
very short ball, and it kept low, Raina makes the adjustment late but get enough meat on the ball to get it away to the midwicket boundary
short ball, Dhoni shimmies down the track, doesn't get bat on the ball, it thuds into his pads and they get a leg bye
another ball that kept low, that was a back of a length, Raina was on the back foot, had to make a late-adjustment to defend that one
Raina guides it towards backward point
short ball again, aimed at the body, Raina keeps it down awkwardly, the ball rolls towards square leg and the batsmen get a single
bouncer and Dhoni goes for the pull, doesn't get hold of it and it goes towards fine leg for a couple
a much better pull from Dhoni this time, from outside off, ensures the ball is kept down and gets the placement spot-on as well, four runs
fired into legstump, Raina glances it fine leg
short and wide, Dhoni goes for the cut but is beaten

shortish ball, Dhoni gets a big stride in and pokes at it, the ball goes through to the keeper, huge appeal, first for caught-behind and then for a stumping ... given not out after many replays proved inconclusive, Dhoni gets the benefit of the doubt
walks down the track and aims to play it to the leg side, ball raps his pads
gets across and glances it to backward square leg
Raina gets on the front foot and defends it towards cover
goes for a drive outside off and get an inside-edge, but all is well
short of a length, Dhoni covers off stump and pushes a single to midwicket, and thats India's 200 up in the 34th over
pitches on a length and Raina gets in line to defend it back
gets forward and drives this one to the man stationed at cover
plays across his stumps and gets struck outside the line of impact, there was a noise as well so could have been a thin inside edge there as well, no appeal
pitches fuller  and Dhoni drives down the ground to keep strike
tossed up, Dhoni strides forward and defends it back
shuffles and works this one towards the leg side
tossed up on a length, he gets forward and pushes to point
strides a long way forward and turns this from outside off to midwicket
speared into Raina's legs, he shuffles and on-drives to the fielder
flatter and a tad shorter and Raina plays it to the off side
starts to move down, Harmison sees him and drops it short, Dhoni holds back the bat and looks on as the ball gains on him en route to Prior
now he pitches full and Dhoni twirls the ball into the covers, easily stopped
short outside off stump, Dhoni flays the bat in an attempt to square cut the ball but it stays low and skims underneath it, more awkward bounce
short of a length, cracked off the back foot, cover runs in and stops
change of pace, fuller too, Dhoni pinches a single to mid-on
changes the angle and runs in from around the stumps, bowls short into Raina, who shuffles and turns it off the hips, in the air through short fine leg for one
full and flat, Raina on-drives with a flourish down to long-on
tossed up on a length, Dhoni gets a stride in and drives to mid-on

oh thats lucky for Dhoni, who closes the bat face to a low full toss and gets a leading edge that pops up over the bowler and drops between mid-on and mid-off
full and flat, Dhoni skips out and drives hard towards mid-on
short and Raina drives into the covers to end the over
well outside off, Raina reaches for that and cuts it towards sweeper cover
pitched up, on middle, Dhoni times that straight drive to perfection, it runs into a heap of sawdust but still has the legs to reach the boundary
slower ball, a bit of width, Dhoni carves that through covers for a couple
back of a length, angling into Dhoni, who defends it to mid-off
on the pads, turned to deep square leg
pitched up, driven to covers, straight to the fielder so there's no run to be taken
back of a length, pitching outside off,  Dhoni backs away and cuts it to cover
Raina gets an inside edge as he tries to work it to long-off, the ball runs away towards midwicket
overpitched delivery, Dhoni hammers it but straight to the fielder at mid-off
high full toss, Raina was coming down the pitch, he was surprised by the full toss but punches it back over the bowler's head for a boundary
a lower full toss this time, no change in the result, Raina comes down the track and lofts it over the bowler's head for another four
turns it to square leg for a single
starts off with a beauty, back of a length, just outside off, Raina' tries to defend off the back foot but is beaten
a bit wider than the previous one, Raina steers that behind point for a boundary, great placement from Raina
short ball on off, played with soft hands by Raina towards cover point, batsmen pinch a quick single
not much width for Dhoni to work with but he crashes it off the backfoot past point, superb timing on that shot
full delivery, on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
Dhoni is beaten as he tries to guide one towards third man
pitched up, on middle and leg, worked to long-off for a single
length ball, Dhoni pushes it towards cover, there's some confusion in the calling before the batsmen decide against taking the single
strays onto leg stump, Dhoni swipes it behind square for a single
Raina comes down the track and flicks a full ball to midwicket
overpitched, and Dhoni crunches it down the ground, just to the left of the bowler for a boundary, that's his half-century
Dhoni's gone, trapped lbw, dances down the track, and looks to hoick him over midwicket, misses the ball completely, rapped on the pads, and the umpire gives it
drags it short, Raina doesn't bother much with his footwork as he slams it to the midwicket boundary
the dew is causing trouble here, the ball slips out of Bopara's hand and comes out as a high full toss to Raina, who manges to get out of it's way
length ball outside off, defended by Rohit towards backward point
turned towards midwicket by Rohit, he gets off the mark
overpitched and outside off, Raina drives that down to long-off for a single
a bit of extra bounce for Bopara, Rohit guides it towards short third man for a single
Raina tickles it down the leg side for a boundary, and that brings up his half-century
worked down to long-on for a single
that was a short one outside off, Raina flatbats it down to long-off
tossed up, full and just outside off, Rohit digs it out towards cover point
driven to long-on for a single
punched off the backfoot to extra cover
and a bouncer from the offspinner, thats so high that it's called a wide
punched off the backfoot to extra cover
defended off the front foot
whistling down the leg side, Rohit glances it for two runs
defended to covers off the backfoot
very wide outside off, Rohit slashes it through cover for a boundary, and that's 5-0 to India
